October 7th, 1933.
Mr. P.D.C. Ball,
200 Security Building,
St.
Louis.
U. S. A.
Dear Mr. Ball,
Your letter of July 29th reached me shortly
after my return from Manila, but the party whom I wanted
to talk to about representing you here, was out of the
city, and only just now I had the opportuhity of hearing
from him as per letter enclosed herewith.
You remember that when I
came out here you
gave me the name of Carl Nahmmacher as a possible representative
of Monocoupe in China.
During my long stay in China I have
become very well acquainted with Nahmmacher and his partner
L. A. Lewis.
As a matter of fact, while Nanhmmacher and
Lewis are partners, they operate separately by reason of the
fact that Nahmmacher is the representative of United Air-
Transport, and that Company does not permit their representa-
tive to handle any other line, therefore Lewis acts as repre-
sentative for she Fleet likoomyeny and he woula also have to
act for Monocoupe. I have no reservation whatever with regard
to the integrity of either Nahmmacher or Lewis. They have done
fairly well in China, recently having sold 6 fleets and 15
Boeing Pursuits, and previously sold 30 fleets to the, School
in Hangchow.
Their financial
responsibility is somewhat limited,
They run a garage which is their bread and butter and the
aviation business, I would say, is the cake.
In my opnion, you
would be perfectly safe in sending a Monocoupe out here on
SENTO, (SIAOS
